task.summary:
Create the basic functions in algorithm and genotype
Created the wave function measurement for all individuals and added comments for TODO things. Created the initialization of parameters fo genotype and added the measure function for measuring the qRegister state. Questions arised about the measurement vector type. If a bool vector is used, it's harder to use this algorithm in existing problems. The solution is 'Binary' but it's storage method is weird and unintuitive. Further investigation is needed.

Add QuantumLookupTable, implement the QIGA, problems with Binary
Added the QuantumLookupTable class and an empty method. Implemented the QIGA adding necessary method calls and evaluations. Made QuantumRegister extend Binary and hold a vector<double> alphas_. When running the program it randomizes correctly (I guess) and finds awesome fitness results, but the calculated and found solution for function 1 don't add up.

Update the algorithm
The algorithm was reorganized to match the one from Wiki page. The register is also tweaked to suffice ECF's runtime workflow and replaced the alphas variable with thetas, adjusting with the initializer and measurment methods.
The quantum rotation gate still needs implementation.

Initialize the quantum rotation gate basics
Added the standard direction table and the adaptive rotation calculator.
Still need to calculate and implement the qRotation gate for register with thetas and resolve some issues with the look-up table.

Implement the quantum rotation gate and perform first tests
Implemented the test version of the quantum rotation gate. The program now runs. Still need to enable extraction of some variables into the config file.
The first tests are quite sad. The algorithm bounces around the best solution as expected. On first look it behaves like a completely random space search. The algorithm still needs some additions like crossover and mutation to help it, but I have little hope about it. I think it needs some 'focusing' operators to stabilize the randomness.
Also, it needs a complete theory debugging. Something about the directions table makes me uncomfortable so I'll compute a few examples on paper.

Fix QIGA disaster bug and update graphs
The QIGA disaster operator called the initialize method which kept increasing the thetas array size, resulting in a exponential slowdown of the algorithm. Now that it's fixed, algorithm purrs like a kitten.
Updated the scripts and jars for graphs, removed extras. Script can now be called with a 'only display results' mode (-d) and send notification on Slack upon completion (-n). Those .log and .tmp files are used for the graph and should not be edited. They'll get removed and updated when starting a new comparison test. BE SURE TO CHANGE THE HOOK ID AND CHANNEL NAME BEFORE UPLOADING TO SLACK.
Knapsack problem works for QIGA. The classical knapsack however, doesn't work. It gets stuck on the first iteration.
Finally, added some knapsack testing files and reorganized the project.

Fix cast adapter a bug in Knapsack and add NN
Fixed the casting and value copying from the qRegisters in QIGA to the user defined genotipe. Supporting Binary, BitString and FloatingPoint.
Knapsack had iteration problems, now it's fixed. Added support for BitString. SteadyStateTournament doesn't work (loops somewhere in the algorithm).
Added the NeuralNetwork genotype and created the test parameters for QIGA. Classical outperforms quantum in both fitness and generation.
Add Knapsack generator, generated problems and fix bugs in QIGA and rotation gate
Create a unit testing framework and fix random directions in QuantumRotationGate
